title.narrative: 5.1 INCREASED CAPACITY TO DESIGN-IMPLEMET SOCIAL POLICIES AND SOCIAL PROTECTION

description.narrative: Increased capacity to design-implement social policies and social protection, which contributes to Access To Inclusive Social Protection, Access To Inclusive Social Protection (Covid), Cross Sectoral - Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews (Covid), Evaluation, Reducing Child Poverty, Research, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022, more vulnerable children have access to social protection systems and are supported to participate in society and realize their rights

title.narrative: Increased capacity to design-implement social policies and social protection

description.narrative: UNICEF supported the development of a National Action Plan to implement the CRC Concluding Observations which in 2021 focused on the publication of the CRC in the national Gazette and drafting the State Party reports on the CRC optional protocols. In Social Protection, UNICEF delivered the first of four monthly Child Cash Grant payments to 1,160 households whose homes were damaged or destroyed during the May 2021 escalation in Gaza, as well as a one-off cash transfer to 687 households made newly vulnerable due to COVID-19. Partner capacity building continued focused on AAP, M&E and financial systems and policies. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:19/01/2022
